******
[2] Shaanxi
Date: Wed 7 Jun 2017 11:52 AM
Source: FIC (Flu Information Centre/Flu in China) [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news-19495.html


According to the HFPB [Health and Family Planning Bureau] of Yulin city, Shaanxi province, a 67-year-old male farmer, (husband of the 1st imported case), resident of Tuke town of Uxin Banner of Ordos city of Inner Mongolia municipality, confirmed to be the 2nd imported human H7N9 AIV case in Yulin city on [Tue 6 Jun 2017]. The patient had sick/dead poultry contact history prior to the onset of symptoms. The patient and his wife developed symptoms such as cough and fever, and was not improved after treatment in the local clinic. Both patients went to a hospital in Yuyang district of Yulin city for treatment on the afternoon of [Mon 29 May 2017] and were transferred to the city Chinese medicine hospital as suspected human H7N9 case.

The Yulin city CDC tested his samples on [Mon 29 May, Sun 4, and Tue 6 Jun 2017] separately. His samples tested positive for H7N9 AIV by Yulin city CDC on [Tue 6 Jun 2017]. The patient is now receiving treatment and quarantine in the hospital.

