[3] Shanxi
Date: Sat 10 Jun 2017 10:43 AM
Source: FIC (Flu Information Centre/Flu in China) [edited]
http://www.flu.org.cn/en/news_detail?action=ql&uid=&pd=&newsId=19506


According to the HFPC of Shanxi province, Datong city reported one exported human H7N9 case on [Mon 5 Jun 2017].

The 55-year-old female patient, resident of Datong county of Datong city, was confirmed to be human H7N9 AIV case by Beijing CDC on [Mon 5 Jun 2017]. He remained in the designated hospital for treatment and quarantine. [Note, the gender of this patient is not clear from the report as the report says "55-year-old female.." but then says "He remained...". - Mod.MPP]

